Algorithm Description for Expense Tracking and Analysis System
Algorithm Name
Expense Recording and Analysis Algorithm
Objective
To store daily expense records, categorize them, calculate total expenses, and generate category-wise analysis using pivot summary.
Step-by-Step Algorithm
Step 1: Start
Begin the expense tracking process.
Step 2: Input Expense Details
Take the following input from the user:
Date
Month
Category
Amount
Description
Payment Method
Example:
Date = 01/10/2023
Category = Groceries
Amount = 150
Step 3: Validate Input
Check whether:
Date is valid
Amount is numeric and greater than 0
Category is not empty
Payment method is selected
If invalid, show error and ask for re-entry.
Step 4: Store Data
Save the entered data as a new record in the expense dataset.
Example record format:
(Date, Month, Category, Amount, Description, Payment Method)
Step 5: Repeat for All Expenses
Continue adding records until all expenses are entered.
Step 6: Categorize Expenses
Group expenses according to categories such as:
Groceries
Utilities
Entertainment
Transport
Healthcare
Education
Shopping
Step 7: Calculate Total Expense
Compute total spending using:
Total Expense=∑Amount
This means adding all expense amounts.
Example:
150 + 75.5 + 20 + 45 = Total
Step 8: Category-wise Analysis
For each category:
Sum all amounts belonging to that category
Count number of transactions
Formula:
Category Total=∑Amount of selected category
This is what your pivot table sheet is doing.
Example:
Groceries = 150 + 160 + ...
Step 9: Monthly Analysis
Group data month-wise using the Month column.
Calculate:
Monthly Expense=∑Amount for same month
This helps compare monthly spending.
Step 10: Generate Pivot Table Summary
Create a pivot table with:
Rows = Category / Description
Values = Sum of Amount
This provides summarized analysis.
Step 11: Display Results
Show:
Total expenses
Category-wise totals
Monthly totals
Highest expense category
Step 12: End
Stop the process.
Simple Pseudocode
START

Input expense details
Validate input

IF input is valid THEN
    Store record
ELSE
    Show error
END IF

FOR each category
    Calculate sum of amount
END FOR

FOR each month
    Calculate monthly total
END FOR

Generate pivot table summary
Display analysis report

STOP
